    "Up to 49.56 % of the pressure increase at the centre of the downstream surface is obtained in the PM-Dynamic case, while only 21.15 % can be achieved by a static feedback controller.",
    "In figure 6(b), the base pressure RMS is shown.",
    "For the baseline flow, strong vortex-induced fluctuations of the base pressure can be noticed around the top and bottom on the downstream surface of the bluff body.",
    "In the PM-Static case, the RL controller partially suppresses the vortex shedding, leading to a sub-optimal reduction of the pressure fluctuation.",
    "The sensors close to the top and bottom corners are also affected by the synthetic jets, which change the RMS trend for the two top and bottom measurements."
